                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/25076b: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Henderson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-10-24T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >October 24, 1942—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>537. Information has come to the British Government indicating that one or
                    possibly more of the French ships referred to in the Department’s telegram No.
                    535 to Kuibyshev may arrive soon at the Dardanelles. Please make every attempt
                    to obtain the views of the Soviet Government regarding the questions raised in
                    the above-mentioned telegram at the earliest possible moment and inform both
                    Ankara and Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
